parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The excessive oil consumption can cause the engine to seize, leading to accidents, injuries, or fatalities, especially if the vehicle stalls in traffic or on a busy highway.
symptoms: The vehicle consumes excessive amounts of oil between oil changes
often requiring the addition of 1-2 quarts of oil every 1
000 miles. The oil level may drop below the minimum mark on the dipstick
and the oil light may not come on until the oil level is critically low.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden shattering of the sunroof can cause glass to fall into the vehicle, potentially injuring occupants and obstructing the driver's view, leading to accidents or loss of control.
Excessive oil consumption can lead to engine failure, causing the vehicle to shut down or catch fire, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: Vehicle burning oil at an increasingly fast rate
no oil light or dashboard warning

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Poorly Designed and Faulty Body Components
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Faulty body components can lead to accidents, injuries, or fatalities due to compromised vehicle safety and structural integrity.
symptoms: Rear hatch breaking off under normal wear and tear

parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Wind Deflector and Sunroof Glass Shattering
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: Shattering wind deflectors and sunroof glass can cause injuries, accidents, or fatalities due to flying glass debris.
symptoms: Wind deflector shattering into many pieces
and glass raining down around the driver.
